Best Model¶

Model 1 is the best model, because

Model 1 has a higher Box(P) value for the all class, as well as for the very_poor class. The mAP50 value for the all class is also higher for Model 1. Additionally, the speed of Model 1 is faster than Model 7 (closest to model 1) in terms of preprocess, inference, loss, and postprocess per image.

Based on these observations, Model 1 is the better choice in terms of performance and speed.
